æ%    Magnitude, a measure of the brightness of a star - the Ancient  Greek    æ%
æ%    astronomers divided  the stars  into six  magnitudes. First-magnitude    æ%
æ%    stars  were  the  brightest,  and  sixth-magnitude  stars  were   the    æ%
æ%    faintest. This system has been kept in modern times, when the new era    æ%
æ%    of MAGNiTUDE has started.                                                æ%
æ%                                                                             æ%
